The paper deals with information theory and communication networks, which are typically covered in the cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-categories. The use of compress-and-forward (CAF) schemes and the study of capacity bounds also suggest the cs.SI (Systems and Control) sub-category. The paper also involves some algebraic manipulation and analysis of specific channel models, which could fall under the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category. Finally, the study of a relay channel with binary multiplicative states and binary additive noise suggests the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category, which deals with the processing and transmission of multimedia data.
